																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>Going to the gym is not everyoneâ€™s favorite part of the day, especially during peak gym times. The crowded gym can be overstimulating and limit access to equipment needed for that dayâ€™s workout. Thatâ€™s why home gyms, especially post-pandemic, have become so popular.</p>



<p>Adding an at-home back workout to your home gym training sessions can greatly improve muscle mass and strength. Training back muscles like the latissimus dorsi and erector spinae will help stimulate the hypertrophy needed to better support posture.&nbsp;</p>



<div class="wp-block-group box-grey is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">10 Best Back Workouts To Do At Home</p>



<p>For a superior at-home back workout, utilize exercises like the ones listed below.&nbsp;</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Wide-Grip-Pull-Up">Wide-grip pull-up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Chair-Inverted-Row">Chair inverted row.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Superman">Superman.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Prone-W-To-Y">Prone W to Y.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Bird-Dog">Bird dog.&nbsp;</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Deadlift">Dumbbell deadlift.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Bent-Over-Row">Dumbbell bent-over row.&nbsp;</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Pullover">Dumbbell pullover.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Seated-Rear-Delt-Fly">Dumbbell seated rear-delt fly.&nbsp;</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Shrug">Dumbbell shrug.&nbsp;</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">5 Best At-Home Bodyweight Back Workouts</h2>



<p>If you donâ€™t have gym equipment but desperately want to improve your health and fitness, donâ€™t worry. Use these top <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/bodyweight-back-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">bodyweight back exercises</a> to strengthen your upper body.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Wide-Grip-Pull-Up">Wide-Grip Pull-Up</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/wide-grip-pull-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Wide-grip pull-ups</a> are a variation of the traditional pull-up, enforcing a broader hand grip position. This <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24662157/#:~:text=In%20the%20eccentric%20phase%2C%20there%20was%20greater%20activation%20using%20wide%20vs.%20narrow%20grip%20for%20latissimus%20and%20infraspinatus%20(p%20%E2%89%A4%200.04)%2C%20and%20tendencies%20for%20medium%20greater%20than%20narrow%20for%20latissimus%2C%20and%20medium%20greater%20than%20wide%20for%20biceps%20(both%20p%20%3D%200.08)%2C%20was%20observed." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">increases the activation</a> of other muscles like the latissimus dorsi and infraspinatus. Like the traditional version, the wide-grip pull-up integrates muscles like the erector spinae, trapezius, rhomboids, and core, as well.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In the wide-grip pull-up, these muscles must fight against gravity and the lifterâ€™s body weight to reach the bar. Altogether, the pull-up and its variations are proactive in <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10813506/#:~:text=Our%20study%20revealed%20that%20a%205%2Dweek%20training%20period%20based%20on%20pull%2Dups%20is%20effective%20in%20improving%20arm%20muscle%20power%2C%20body%20coordination%2C%20and%20arm%20endurance%2C%20resulting%20in%20significant%20performance%20ranging%20from%20%2B5%25%20to%20%2B21.9%25." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">enhancing total body composition</a> and arm muscle power.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Wide-Grip Pull-Ups" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/981056606?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Wide-Grip Pull-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Depending on your equipment, you may have a pull-up on a squat rack or a mount set-up.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Move to the bar and use a footstep, like a bench or box, to reach the bar.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Grip the bar in an overhand (palms facing forward) grip.</li>



<li>Widen your hands past shoulder-width to create a <em>Y</em>.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Step off your footstep.</li>



<li>Straighten the arms to hang from the bar. This is your starting position.</li>



<li>Inhale.</li>



<li>Exhale and push the elbows downwards toward the floor.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pull up until your chin passes the bar.</li>



<li>Pause.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and return to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Activate the glutes and core, tensing these muscles to deter swaying or swinging during the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Prioritize a mind-to-muscle connection to <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26700744/#:~:text=Resistance%2Dtrained%20individuals%20can%20increase%20triceps%20brachii%20or%20pectarilis%20major%20muscle%20activity%20during%20the%20bench%20press%20when%20focusing%20on%20using%20the%20specific%20muscle%20at%20intensities%20up%20to%2060%20%25%20of%201RM." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">increase muscle engagement</a>. Think of specifically using the back muscles to produce and stabilize movement.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4â€“6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8â€“12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">12â€“20</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3â€“5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1â€“3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Wide-Grip Pull-Up</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Chair-Inverted-Row">Chair Inverted Row</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/chair-inverted-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chair inverted rows</a> are a modifiable variation of the inverted row when equipment is limited. For home gym workouts, it is accessible for lifters wanting to improve their upper-body strength and fitness.&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26422610/#:~:text=Four%20inverted%20row%20exercises%20activated%20the%20LD%2C%20UT%2C%20MT%2C%20LT%2C%20and%20BB%20at%20levels%20conducive%20to%20strengthening." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Upper body muscles</a> like the trapezius, rhomboids, latissimus dorsi, deltoids, and biceps brachii are engaged. In the inverted row and its variations, <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/269347890_The_Inverted_Row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">spinal stability can be improved</a> to help reduce back pain. For at-home workouts, the chair inverted row is an excellent addition for training and strengthening the back.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Chair Inverted Rows" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980242301?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Chair Inverted Row Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab two chairs and a short bar for the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Move the chairs so that the backs face each other. Leave enough space between the chairs for you.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Sit between the chairs.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Bend your knees with your feet flat on the floor.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Place the bar on top of the backs of both chairs.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Clasp the bar in an overhand grip about shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Straighten your arms to lower yourself down to the floor or as close as possible. This is your starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and pull your torso up to the bar.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause when your chest touches the bar.</li>



<li>Inhale as you return to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Refrain from flaring the elbows out to the sides while performing the chair inverted row. This isnâ€™t considered proper form as it can place avoidable tension on the joints, risking injury. Instead, drive the elbows down to the floor behind you.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Avoid dipping the neck forward. Keep the neck in line to maintain a neutral spine and position to prevent stress on the neck.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



