<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">5 Best Home Back Workouts With Equipment</h2>



<p>Most home gym owners have dumbbells they can implement into their workouts by modifying exercises. These <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-back-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell back exercises</a> are a worthy addition to your home workouts.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Deadlift">Dumbbell Deadlift</h3>



<p>The dumbbell <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7046193/#:~:text=Currently%2C%20Deadlift%20is%20an%20exercise%20frequently%20performed%20to%20improve%20the%20lower%20limb%20muscles%2C%20mainly%20biceps%20femoris%20and%20semitendinosus%20(hamstrings)%2C%20and%20gluteus%20maximus." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">deadlift</a> emphasizes the use of the quadriceps, glutes, and hamstrings. Other muscle groups used include the erector spinae, calves, and latissimus dorsi.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Implementing the <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-deadlift" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell deadlift</a> into your home gym training can be beneficial for improving strength in the upper and lower body. <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4499985/#:~:text=Additionally%2C%20the%20muscle%20strength%20is%20lower%20in%20female%20individuals%20than%20in%20male%20individuals%3B%20therefore%2C%20female%20individuals%20have%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20posture%20imbalance.%20To%20reduce%20such%20risk%2C%20the%20increase%20of%20muscle%20strength%20and%20flexibility%20through%20regular%20overload%20exercise%20is%20necessary13)." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Proper posture</a> can be more easily maintained with stronger back muscles, which provide spinal support and stability.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Deadlift" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1003966832?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Deadlift Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>You will need two dumbbells for this exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hold the dumbbells in an overhand grip at your thighs.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stand with feet hip-width apart. This is your starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and hinge at the hips, pushing them back to lean the torso forward.&nbsp;</li>



<li>As the torso tilts forward, allow the dumbbells to travel down the leg.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause when they reach the middle of the shins.</li>



<li>Exhale and return to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a neutral spine, refraining from arching the neck to look up.</li>



<li>Keep the feet flat on the floor. Press through the feet to return to the starting position to increase muscle engagement in the legs.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



