</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Pullover">Dumbbell Pullover</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-pullover" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell pullover</a> is frequently used to train the pectorals and latissimus dorsi. It activates other muscle groups like the triceps, teres major, serratus anterior, and core to stabilize and produce movement.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The dumbbell pullover was shown to have significant <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/353646302_Electromyographic_Activation_of_Pectoralis_Major_and_Triceps_Brachii_during_Dumbbell_Pullover#:~:text=It%20was%20concluded%20that%20TB%20showed%20greater%20muscle%20activation%20in%20the%20dumbbell%20pullover%20exercise%2C%20regardless%20of%20elbow%20position.%20Also%2C%20the%20dumbbell%20pullover%20with%20elbow%20extension%20showed%20greater%20PMS%20muscle%20activation." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">triceps brachii activation</a> and, with straight elbows, pectoralis major engagement. The barbell pullover recruited <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/365077201_Comparison_of_Electromyographic_Activity_during_Barbell_Pullover_and_Straight_Arm_Pulldown_Exercises#:~:text=In%20conclusion%2C%20the,the%20evaluated%20muscles." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">more of the pectoralis major</a> than latissimus dorsi. Although it doesnâ€™t have a greater activation rate in back muscles like the latissimus dorsi, it still integrates them.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
