</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Shrug Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab two dumbbells for the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stand with feet hip-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hold the dumbbells at your sides with palms facing you. This is your starting position.</li>



<li>Inhale.</li>



<li>Exhale and contract the traps, elevating the shoulders upwards into a shrug.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and return to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Refrain from jutting the head forward as you perform the shrugging motion in the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Ego lifting should be avoided completely, including in this exercise. Prioritize controlled movement over heavy-weight loads.</li>
</ul>



